==English==

===Etymology===
From Spanish meaning "hat" which in turn comes from Vulgar Latin "sub" meaning "under" and "umbra" meaning "shadow".

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[File:Sombrero (PSF).png|thumb|sombrero]]

# The sombrero [[hat]] has a high conical or cylindrical crown with a saucer-shaped brim, highly embroidered made of plush felt.
# A mixed drink with [[tequila]], named after the Mexican hat.

